TY  - JOUR
AU  - Beggs, A. W.
T1  - Queues and Hierarchies
PY  - 2001
Y1  - 2001/04/01
DO  - 10.1111/1467-937X.00170
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 68
IS  - 2
SP  - 297
EP  - 322
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper examines the optimal structure of hierarchies when workers differ in the range of tasks they can perform. A hierarchical system may reduce costs by allowing most tasks to be handled by unskilled workers. This may however increase delay for those tasks which must pass through several layers before reaching the appropriate level. The paper characterises an optimal hierarchy when such a trade-off exists.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1467-937X.00170
ER  - 



