TY  - JOUR
AU  - Rey, Hélène
T1  - International Trade and Currency Exchange
PY  - 2001
Y1  - 2001/04/01
DO  - 10.1111/1467-937X.00176
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 68
IS  - 2
SP  - 443
EP  - 464
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - On the international scene, away from national legal rules, the use of different currencies is largely due to the operation of the “Invisible Hand” The paper develops a three-country model of the world economy. This links real trade patterns with currency exchange structures in a general equilibrium framework which includes transaction costs on foreign exchange markets. In the presence of strategic complementarities, there are multiple equilibrium structures of currency exchange for a given underlying real trade pattern. The existence conditions of these different equilibria are characterized, using the trade links between countries as the key parameters. Finally, repercussions on world output of the choice of a currency exchange structure are analysed.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1467-937X.00176
ER  - 



