TY  - JOUR
AU  - Blouin, Max R.
AU  - Serrano, Roberto
T1  - A Decentralized Market with Common Values Uncertainty: Non-Steady States
PY  - 2001
Y1  - 2001/04/01
DO  - 10.1111/1467-937X.00171
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 68
IS  - 2
SP  - 323
EP  - 346
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We analyse a market where (i) trade proceeds by random and anonymous pairwise meetings with bargaining; (ii) agents are asymmetrically informed about the value of the traded good; and (iii) no new entrants are allowed once the market is open. We show that information revelation and efficiency never obtain in equilibrium, even as discounting is removed. This holds whether the asymmetry is two-sided or one-sided. In some cases there exist equilibria where a substantial amount goes untraded. This contrasts with the earlier literature, which was based on the steadystate equilibria of a model where agents enter the market every period.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1467-937X.00171
ER  - 



